                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.51/1554: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hood</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-09-27T15:00:00-00:44">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 27, 1922—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 4:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>33. About $40,000 of hut tax coming in has given temporary relief and crisis is
                    at least postponed.</p>
                <p>Liberian Government anxious to know when the Senate will adjourn <hi
                        rend="italic">sine die</hi> and whether there is definite reason to believe
                    Liberian loan bill be acted upon before final adjournment of this session.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hood</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
